 Aimuan was a young and vibrant 33-year old lecturer who was working at the University of Benin before he was assassinated by unknown gunmen in Ishior, Benin City. The deceased who was a lecturer in the Department of Public Administration was shot dead on Saturday, June 12, while he was driving into his compound in Isihor, Benin City. It was gathered that the suspected gunmen shot the Uniben assistant lecturer repeatedly before fleeing away from the scene. He was rushed to the hospital where he was confirmed dead. Aimuan was admitted into the institution in 2015 as a Graduate Assistant, reportedly parted with his friends that evening, after an outing around the Ugbowo area before he was murdered. The public relations officer of the university, Benedicta Ehanire, who confirmed the incident described that the late lecturer was a hardworking and very dedicated university staff. Ehanire called on security agents to unravel those behind the killing. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-9902" src="https://i1.wp.com/mlpthjcvvzze.i.optimole.com/qdpMrCw.2zvi~5f0f9/w:auto/h:auto/q:90/https://i2.wp.com/ebitu.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot_2021-04-11_at_3.10.45_PM-removebg-preview.png?resize=84%2C32&#038;ssl=1" alt="EBITU | #EbituBlog" width="84" height="32" data-recalc-dims="1" data-recalc-dims="1"> The post UNIBEN ASSISTANT LECTURER SHOT DEAD appeared first on E B I T Uâ„¢.